President Biden has announced his intention to nominate Bridget A. Brink as the U.S. Ambassador to Ukraine. Brink is currently serving as the U.S. Ambassador to the Slovak Republic and has a long career in the Foreign Service, focusing on Europe and Eurasia. She has held various positions in the U.S. Department of State, including Senior Advisor and Deputy Assistant Secretary in the Bureau of European and Eurasian Affairs. Brink has also served as Deputy Chief of Mission at U.S. Embassies in Uzbekistan and Georgia. She has a Master's degree in International Relations and Political Theory and speaks Russian, Slovak, Serbian, Georgian, and French.